ClsC_30c8f815.class_description: Operating and loading conditions that drive thermal fatigue in metallic components, including cyclic stresses arising from temperature changes and repeated thermal cycling.
ClsC_30c8f815.evidence_excerpt: Thermal fatigue is the result of cyclic stresses caused by variations in temperature... particularly under repeated thermal cycling.

members.entity_description: Repeatedly varying mechanical stresses that arise due to changing temperatures in components.
members.resolution_context: Thermal fatigue is the result of cyclic stresses caused by variations in temperature. These cyclic stresses contribute to cracking in metallic components where movement or expansion is constrained.

members.entity_description: Changes in temperature over time that induce cyclic stresses in metallic components.
members.resolution_context: Thermal fatigue is the result of cyclic stresses caused by variations in temperature. These temperature variations lead to repeated expansion and contraction, especially under repeated thermal cycling.

members.entity_description: Repeated heating and cooling cycles that subject components to alternating thermal stresses.
members.resolution_context: Damage is in the form of cracking that may occur anywhere in a metallic component where relative movement or differential expansion is constrained, particularly under repeated thermal cycling.

ClsC_c81dcb41.class_description: Physical phenomena involving constrained mechanical or thermal deformation between regions or parts of a component (such as relative movement or differential expansion) that can lead to cracking, especially under repeated thermal cycling.
ClsC_c81dcb41.evidence_excerpt: Cracking may occur where relative movement or differential expansion is constrained, particularly under repeated thermal cycling.

members.entity_description: Mechanical motion between different parts or regions of a component that may be constrained.
members.resolution_context: Damage is in the form of cracking that may occur anywhere in a metallic component where relative movement or differential expansion is constrained, particularly under repeated thermal cycling.

members.entity_description: Non-uniform thermal expansion between different regions of a component that can be constrained.
members.resolution_context: Damage is in the form of cracking that may occur anywhere in a metallic component where relative movement or differential expansion is constrained, particularly under repeated thermal cycling.
